### Akeeba Panopticon API — Sites (read-only)
###
### PhpStorm HTTP Client request file. Use the run gutter icon next to each block
### or right-click → Run All Requests in File.
###
### Replace the env vars below or define them in a sibling `http-client.env.json`.

@hostname = https://panopticon.local
@token    = REPLACE-ME-WITH-A-REAL-TOKEN

### List sites (recommended: Bearer auth)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### List sites with filters and pagination
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites?search=example&cmsType=joomla&limit=10&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### Get a single site by id
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/site/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### --- Alternative authentication surfaces -------------------------------------

### Custom header (X-Panopticon-Token)
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites
X-Panopticon-Token: {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### GET parameter — NOT recommended for production.
# WARNING: query-string tokens are leaked through web-server access logs and the
# Referer header. Documented as a footgun in assets/api/docs/overview.md.
# Use Bearer auth in real automations.
GET {{hostname}}/api/v1/sites?_panopticon_token={{token}}
Accept: application/json
